# Salesforce Integration

## Context

The app connects to Salesforce Commercial Office to read **Calls for Resources** — a custom
Salesforce object (`Call_For_Resources__c`) with a child object **Call For Resources Line Items**
(`Call_For_Resources_Line_Item__c`). This data is read-only from the app's perspective.
Nothing is ever written back to Salesforce.

The Salesforce org is the Brussels Capital Region (Paradigm) production instance.
For dev/testing, use a sandbox — set `SF_LOGIN_URL=https://test.salesforce.com`.

---

## Library

Use **`jsforce`** — the only supported Salesforce client library in this project.

```bash
npm install jsforce
npm install --save-dev @types/jsforce
```

Never use raw `fetch` against the Salesforce REST API. Always go through the `jsforce`
connection from the singleton.

---

## Client Singleton

The connection is managed in `src/lib/salesforce.ts`. Never instantiate `new jsforce.Connection()`
anywhere else.

```ts
// src/lib/salesforce.ts
import jsforce from "jsforce";

let conn: jsforce.Connection | null = null;

export async function getSalesforceConnection(): Promise<jsforce.Connection> {
  if (conn) return conn;

  conn = new jsforce.Connection({
    loginUrl: process.env.SF_LOGIN_URL ?? "https://login.salesforce.com",
  });

  await conn.login(
    process.env.SF_USERNAME!,
    process.env.SF_PASSWORD! + process.env.SF_SECURITY_TOKEN!
  );

  return conn;
}
```

### Auth method

Username + Password + Security Token (server-to-server). The password and security token
are concatenated as a single string — this is the jsforce convention.

```
SF_PASSWORD + SF_SECURITY_TOKEN  →  passed as the second argument to conn.login()
```

---

## Environment Variables

These must be present in `.env.local` (dev) and in the OpenShift Secret (prod).
Never commit real values. The `.env` file contains placeholder strings only.

```env
SF_CLIENT_ID=changeme
SF_CLIENT_SECRET=changeme
SF_USERNAME=changeme@paradigm.brussels
SF_PASSWORD=changeme
SF_SECURITY_TOKEN=changeme
SF_LOGIN_URL=https://login.salesforce.com
# For sandbox: SF_LOGIN_URL=https://test.salesforce.com
```

Add these six variables to `openshift/secret.yaml.example` alongside `DATABASE_URL`.

