## API Name Discovery (run once)

**Before writing any SOQL query**, run the describe script to get exact API field names.
Salesforce UI labels ("Account Name", "WBS", "SAP Product Code") are not the same as
API names. Custom fields end in `__c`; relationship traversal fields end in `__r`.

```ts
// scripts/sf-describe.ts  —  run with: npx tsx scripts/sf-describe.ts
import { getSalesforceConnection } from "../src/lib/salesforce";

async function describe() {
  const conn = await getSalesforceConnection();

  for (const objectName of [
    "Call_For_Resources__c",
    "Call_For_Resources_Line_Item__c",
  ]) {
    const meta = await conn.describe(objectName);
    console.log(`\n=== ${objectName} ===`);
    meta.fields.forEach(f =>
      console.log(`${f.label.padEnd(45)} ${f.name}  (${f.type})`)
    );
  }
}

describe().catch(console.error);
```

Run this against the sandbox first. The output maps every UI label to its API name.
Record the API names in a comment at the top of `src/lib/salesforce-queries.ts` for
future reference — do not rely on memory or guesswork.

